bout 1500 damage per round.<br>
<br>
All of a sudden, a new giant pops just when the puller returns to camp with his single-pull: we have an add.<br>
No biggie, the chanter mezzes one of them, and the group switches back to giant-whacking. That is: the group minus me. What I failed to see, was that the tank had switched targets right after those two giants entered our camp, and that the mob I had targetted now (Giant_01), is NOT the one engaged by our tank: Giant_02.<br>
<br>
So, kinda laid-back, I start off with a nice, light nuke to soften him up a bit, and read the message &quot;A Vann Hellig has been awakened by Etelka&quot;. Oops.<br>
Since that little gnome chanter was still standing right next to his mezzed mob, the second message I read is &quot;Chanter has been slain by a Vann Hellig&quot;. Splat.<br>
<br>
Now things get interesting. <br>
<br>
With the chanter out of the way, Giant_01 makes a beeline for me, and starts hitting.<br>
With no root or snare memmed, I do the only thing that I can think of to stay alive: I start chain-casting my damage-absorption shield on myself. At the same moment the tank is still happily slashing away at Giant_02, and by now the cleric is healing her brains out, trying to keep both of us alive.<br>
<br>
This way, I manage to tank that giant for at least 30 seconds, not realizing that constantly casting that 800-point absorption shield on myself skyrockets me on the agro-list of BOTH giants, while they're quickly building a dislike for that pesky cleric there as well.<br>
<br>
After those 30 seconds, the warrior de-engages his giant to run over to me and taunt my giant off me and try to regain control over the situation. While he runs over, I manage to make it to the top of *his* giant's agro-list as well, so now I can read the message &quot;Giant_02 says You shall not evade me Etelka!&quot;. Great. Summoned by his mob.<br>
Right after I'm summoned thou, I manage to channel through yet another shield, kicking me back to the top of MY giant's agro-list. Sooo.... &quot;Giant_01 says You shall not evade me Etelka!&quot;.<br>
Like a roller-coaster ride, back we go again, to the spot I left half a second before. Now, with both giants wanting to use my guts for interior decoration, this wizzy's tanking abilities are over.<br>
I bravely try and save my ass one last time, but the combined damage of those two monsters rip through my hitpoints like the wet paper towel that is actually is, and the last thing I can see is my corpse from above, two giants totally ignoring the warrior and making a run for the cleric, and the cleric saying &quot;Uh-ooh&quot;.<br>
<br>
